{"chunk_id": "0246b75f-6bad-4a23-80b1-5ab96bcbb1f3", "source_database": "ICMR", "document_title": "ICMR_NIN_Dietary_Guidelines_Real.pdf", "publication_version": "Latest", "chunk_sequence_number": 49, "content_type": "Medical Guideline", "language": "English", "text": "elderly people to enable them to be fit and active. 10 Guideline 1 Eat variety of foods to ensure a balanced diet Rationale: Nutritionally adequate diet should be consumed through a wise choice from a variety of foods /c118Nutrition is a basic prerequisite to sustain life. /c118Variety in food is not only the spice of life but also the essence of nutrition and health. /c118A diet consisting of foods from several food groups provides all the required nutrients in proper amounts. /c118Cereals, millets and pulses are major sources of most nutrients. /c118Milk which provides good quality proteins and calcium must be an essential item of the diet, particularly for infants, children and women. /c118Oils and nuts are calorie-rich foods, and are useful for increasing the energy density and quality", "embedding": [-0.040959183126688004, 0.006236195098608732, -0.002419309224933386, 0.04359005391597748, -0.027427764609456062, 0.046124815940856934, -0.0365300253033638, 0.049255382269620895, -0.03526044264435768, -0.06420215219259262, 0.009591002017259598, -0.024887485429644585, -0.025945359840989113, -0.10825012624263763, -0.04352691024541855, -0.06356431543827057, 0.10359764844179153, 0.020089315250515938, -0.08214165270328522, -0.0796092301607132, 0.01187984086573124, -0.004975385498255491, 0.015896713361144066, -0.009188404306769371, -0.07132527977228165, -0.03824813663959503, -0.02013471908867359, -0.08196406811475754, -0.0326865091919899, 0.07662884145975113, 0.10254932194948196, -0.0002653556293807924, 0.0794341042637825, -0.024227119982242584, -0.08025287091732025, 0.09166619181632996, 0.04159177094697952, -0.11530119925737381, -0.045889537781476974, -0.0014475526986643672, -0.0032960702665150166, -0.014512